Former Prime Minister Raila Odinga has called on the government to craft favorable business policies to allow Kenya to attract more foreign investors. Mr. Odinga was speaking at the launch of a new business platform dubbed invest era plus Africa, a next-generation investment management platform. The new integrated technology-enabled platform aims at simplifying and enhancing entrepreneurs&rsquo; processes, enabling them to capitalize on profitable opportunities quickly and easily. The former premier emphasized the need to grow investments sentiments echoed by business mogul Jimmy Wanjigi who was also present at the launch in Nairobi